  <name>Wys</name>
  <shortname>Wys</shortname>
  <shortdesc>A daemon to bring up and take down PulseAudio loopbacks for phone call audio</shortdesc>
  <description>During a phone call, audio must be streamed from one
  ALSA device to another ALSA device.  This should only happen during
  the call, when the modem's audio interfaces will actually be active.
  To facilitate this, Wys will wait for ModemManager calls in the
  ringing or active state and enable appropriate PulseAudio loopback
  modules only during those states.</description>
